00:18:23.188 --> 00:18:26.948
have evaluated whether this was an effective strategy for RAS

281
00:18:26.958 --> 00:18:30.738
mutant cancers. And what we have seen is that

282
00:18:31.288 --> 00:18:32.738
this agonist for CLPP

283
00:18:33.588 --> 00:18:37.228
was very active against RAS mutant cancer cell lines as well as

284
00:18:37.388 --> 00:18:37.988
organoids.

285
00:18:38.868 --> 00:18:42.448
And we found that if you make cells null to

286
00:18:42.488 --> 00:18:44.908
CLPP, there's a loss of this activity.

287
00:18:45.008 --> 00:18:47.588
So it was a very CLPP-dependent activity.

288
00:18:48.528 --> 00:18:52.028
This agonist results in significant disruption of

289
00:18:52.048 --> 00:18:53.248
